This paper deals with the issue of network address translation (NAT) and its impact on peer-to-peer communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the reliability and robustness of NAT traversal techniques, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also analyzes the security implications of NAT traversal techniques, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of NAT traversal techniques on important P2P applications such as Voice over IP and online gaming protocols, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
